==English==
===Noun===
'''[[foul]] [[wind]]'''
# {{nautical}} A wind blowing against the direction the sailor wants to go, ie. unfavourably.  "Foul" doesn't refer to the strength or character of the wind, only its direction.  (Reference: [[w:Ray Parkin|Ray Parkin]], ''H. M. Bark Endeavour'', [[w:Miegunyah Press|Miegunyah Press]], second edition 2003, ISBN 0-522-85093-6, page 210.)

